      "href": "/henrycovert/list/blaxploitation/",
      "user": "henrycovert",
      "slug": "blaxploitation",
      "title": "Blaxploitation",
      "desc": "These are all of the Blaxploitation films I have seen. Encompasses all sub-genres. Includes films marketed back in the day as blaxploitation that really weren't but deserve to be here for their quality, i.e. Black Jesus, Ganja & Hess. List still in progress.",
      "owner": "List by Henry Covert",
      "tags": []
    },
    {
      "href": "/p_polastri/list/blaxploitation/",
      "user": "p_polastri",
      "slug": "blaxploitation",
      "title": "Blaxploitation",
      "desc": "My favorite blaxploitation movies. For the purpose of this list I define Blaxploitation as Black american cinema between 1968 and 1979 - period in which the production was most intense and the subgenre (of sorts) peaked in popularity.\n\nI take Blaxploitation as a broad definition, thus I won't include strictly exploitation, but also films with predominantly black casts (e.g. Claudine, Cornbread, Earl & Me, Killer of Sheep) and crew, and films dealing with questions concerning race in America (e.g. La Permission, Mandingo, Putney Swope).\n\nEvery movie is an exploitation movie. Every movie tries to get you to part with your eight dollars. Our job is to get you to spend your money, and come into the theater, not unlike a barker…\n\nmore",
      "owner": "List by Paulo Polastri PRO",
      "tags": [
        "genre",
        "usa",
        "blaxploitation",
        "black-cinema"
      ]
    },
